HEADWORD: Wire-pulling
<hw>Wire"-pull`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of pulling the
wires, as of a puppet; hence, secret influence or management, especially
in politics; intrigue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wire-tailed</ent>⟦br⟧
